    caption: [Some freshwater oligochaetes. A, *Stylaria* has the prostomium drawn out into a long snout. B, *Aeolosoma* uses cilia around the mouth to sweep in food particles, and it buds off new individuals asexually. C, *Tubifex* lives head down in long tubes. D, *Dero* has ciliated anal gills.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-11-20-11-57-54.png"
